+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZvociZqb2yqL27iK7BWJ6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive overview:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Overview\n\n### 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── engine.ts       (Build engine with plugin system)\n│   │   ├── index.ts        (Public exports)\n│   │   ├── types.ts        (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   │   └── templates.ts    (HTML templates)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       └── .gitkeep        (Empty - 8 plugins to be created)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts        (15 core engine tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. src/core/ Contents\n\n#### **engine.ts** (117 lines)\nThe `BuildEngine` class is the core of the SSG toolkit. Key features:\n- Registers plugins and templates\n- Topological sort of plugins based on dependencies (`resolvePluginOrder()`)\n- Build pipeline with three phases:\n  1. `beforeBuild` hooks (plugin initialization)\n  2. `transformContent` hooks (file processing)\n  3. `afterBuild` hooks (final output generation)\n- Error handling for circular and missing dependencies\n- Manages a shared `BuildContext` with output files, assets, and plugin data\n\n#### **types.ts** (44 lines)\nCore TypeScript interfaces:\n- `SiteConfig`: Configuration with title, baseUrl, output/content/template directories\n- `ContentFile`: Document with slug, title, content, metadata, optional date/tags/template\n- `BuildContext`: Runtime state with files, output map, assets, and shared data store\n- `PluginHooks`: Optional async hooks (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- `Plugin`: Named plugin with version, dependencies array, and hooks\n- `Template`: Renderer function for HTML templates\n\n#### **templates.ts** (43 lines)\nTwo HTML templates:\n- `createDefaultTemplate()`: Single article layout with title, date, and content\n- `createListTemplate()`: List-based layout for collection pages\n\n#### **index.ts** (4 lines)\nExports the public API: BuildEngine, templates, and all types\n\n---\n\n### 3. Tests Directory - All Test Files\n\n#### **tests/core.test.ts** (195 lines, 15 tests)\nTests the BuildEngine:\n- Plugin registration and retrieval\n- Template registration and rendering\n- Default template with HTML generation\n- List template with special styling\n- Raw content output when no template matches\n- Plugin lifecycle hooks (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Plugin dependency resolution and topological sorting\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multi-plugin transformation chaining\n- Shared data store in context\n- File metadata preservation\n- Empty file list handling\n\n#### **tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts** (91 lines, 8 tests)\nTests markdown → HTML conversion with:\n- Basic markdown (headers, bold, paragraphs)\n- Footnotes with `[^1]` syntax generating superscript links\n- Footnote section rendering at content bottom\n- Admonition containers (:::note, :::warning, :::tip → HTML divs)\n- HTML preservation for existing HTML\n- Empty content handling\n\n#### **tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts** (108 lines, 10 tests)\nTests asset URL rewriting:\n- Rewrites relative image src `./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`\n- Rewrites relative link href `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n- Preserves absolute URLs (https://...)\n- Generates asset-manifest in ctx.data tracking discovered assets\n- Handles files with no assets\n- Processes multiple assets per file\n- Avoids double-processing already-rewritten URLs\n\n#### **tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts** (108 lines, 9 tests)\nTests code block highlighting:\n- Adds `highlighted` class to code blocks with language class\n- Adds `data-language=\"language\"` attribute to pre tags\n- Handles multiple code blocks per file\n- Ignores code blocks without language specification\n- Preserves code block content\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Does not modify inline code (only pre/code blocks)\n\n#### **tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts** (127 lines, 11 tests)\nTests tag/category management:\n- Builds taxonomy-tags Map in ctx.data from file tags\n- Generates tag listing pages in ctx.output (tags/[tagname].html)\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles multiple tags per file\n- Tag pages list all files with that tag\n- Stores tag map in ctx.data as 'taxonomy-tags'\n- Handles empty file lists\n- **Normalizes tags to lowercase** (JavaScript → javascript)\n\n#### **tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts** (121 lines, 8 tests)\nTests RSS 2.0 feed generation:\n- Generates feed.xml with RSS 2.0 structure (`<?xml`, `<rss>`, `<channel>`, `<item>`)\n- Feed items contain HTML content (wrapped in CDATA)\n- Feed items include category tags from taxonomy data\n- Channel title from config.title\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates\n- Feed link uses config.baseUrl for channel and item links\n\n#### **tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts** (115 lines, 8 tests)\nTests searchable JSON index generation:\n- Generates search-index.json in ctx.output\n- Index entries have: slug, title, plain text content\n- HTML tags stripped from indexed content\n- Code block content included in searchable text\n- Handles empty file lists\n- Valid JSON output\n- Includes tags array if present on file\n\n#### **tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts** (102 lines, 9 tests)\nTests XML sitemap generation:\n- Generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output\n- Includes all content page URLs (post-1.html → https://example.com/post-1.html)\n- Includes taxonomy tag pag